					<h1>What is the problem?</h1>
				<p class="desc_text">
				Due to the unsettled political situation in the Ukraine, government funding is
				diverted away from medicine and the field of Anaesthesia, amongst other
				surgical specialities, faces severe cutbacks. Where surgeons are still able
				to operate, the lack of anaesthetic appliances, drugs and equipment cannot
				guarantee a safe anaesthetic procedure – and the cost of this shortage is a
				life. I could not remain indifferent and knew I had to help.
				I went from hospital to hospital to ask for donations of anaesthetic
				appliances which I then sent over a period of time to Zaporozhye and Krivoy
				Rog of Ukraine. This led in turn to buying a couple of second-hand
				ventilators out of one hospital to support one Ukranian ICU. However, this
				all feels like a drop in the ocean and I know that I can, and must, do
				better but I can’t do this alone. I need your help! My idea is to help
				equip my former Ukranian teachers and colleagues with the important
				knowledge and skills that I have gained here in the UK. One of the things
				on the list is to upskill on “Difficult Airways Techniques” or “Ultrasound
				Guided Blocks” courses. Such knowledge will not only help patients by
				providing safer anaesthetics but also reduce complications due to better
				skilled doctors. I will take these courses to the Ukraine, teach my
				colleagues of Advanced Training in Anaesthesia and spread the skills and
				knowledge from hospital to hospital, city to city, showing every
				anaesthetist in the country the advantages of Ultrasound Usage for regional
				anaesthesia and Lines Insertion, together with the different Intubating
				techniques. I would hope to demonstrate to the leaders/managers of
				Ukrainian hospitals the economic benefits of having such knowledge and
				equipment in their hospitals. Of course, this all requires funding to bring
				in specialist equipment, even second hand and this is where I need your
				generous help in order to set up my proposed courses. My project will need
				money for the necessary anaesthetic equipment, dummies to demonstrate the
